    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d169fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London,
                        via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-16">July 16,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 318 from the President to the <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval
                        Person</gloss> secret and personal.</p>
                <p>I have still heard nothing from <gloss target="#t_UJ1">U.J.</gloss> I wired him
                    yesterday and should have an answer quickly. When I hear I will let you know at
                    once about <gloss target="#t_Abraham1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Abraham</hi>
                    </gloss> and I like your suggested time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
